<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-03T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="597" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d597">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72115/3364</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MJVA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-03T13:00:00+08:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 3, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 3, 11.40
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your August 1, 7 p.m. In pursuance of your July 16, 8 [<hi rend="italic">4</hi>] p.m.,<note n="1" xml:id="d597fn1">Not
                                    printed; instructing the Minister “to agree to the proposal of
                                    the Chinese Government provided other interested Governments
                                    agree.” (File No. 763.72115/3342.)</note> the Legation has
                                already signified our Government’s agreement to the Chinese
                                proposal, and British Minister, as senior Allied representative, has
                                conveyed to Foreign Office acceptance of proposals concerning
                                internment and passport control on the part of all Allied Legations
                                other than Belgian.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MJVA1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>